wikipedia_page.main: Thomas Rushby (6 September 1880 at Stoke d'Abernon, Cobham, Surrey – 13 July 1962 at Ewell, Surrey) was an English cricketer. He was a right-arm fast-medium bowler who played for Surrey from 1903 to 1921. In all first-class matches, he took 954 wickets at an average of 20.58. In his final season, he took all ten wickets for 43 runs in the Somerset first innings at Taunton.
